## 7. Zoom Configuration

### 7.1 Zoom Limits

| Parameter | Value | Notes |
|-----------|-------|-------|
| Minimum | 0.05x | Show full 12-year dataset |
| Maximum | 5.0x | Detailed day-level view |
| Initial | 1.0x | Default working view |
| Wheel sensitivity | 0.002 | Multiplier for deltaY |

### 7.2 deck.gl Zoom Conversion

deck.gl uses logarithmic zoom (base 2):

```typescript
// Linear to deck.gl zoom
function linearToDeckZoom(linearZoom: number): number {
  return Math.log2(linearZoom);
}

// deck.gl to linear zoom
function deckZoomToLinear(deckZoom: number): number {
  return Math.pow(2, deckZoom);
}

// Examples:
// linear 0.5 => deck -1
// linear 1.0 => deck 0
// linear 2.0 => deck 1
// linear 4.0 => deck 2
```

### 7.3 Dynamic Minimum Zoom

Calculate minimum zoom to prevent white space:

```typescript
function calculateMinZoom(
  canvasWidth: number,
  canvasHeight: number,
  worldBounds: WorldBounds
): number {
  const worldWidth = worldBounds.maxX - worldBounds.minX;
  const worldHeight = Math.abs(worldBounds.maxY - worldBounds.minY);

  const minZoomX = canvasWidth / worldWidth;
  const minZoomY = canvasHeight / worldHeight;

  // Use larger to fill viewport, floor at 0.05
  return Math.max(Math.max(minZoomX, minZoomY), 0.05);
}
```

